  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study is to examine the suitability to detect diabetic neuropathy using NIR
      and impedance.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study is to examine how suitable a hand-held measuring probe (DDD-probe) using
      NIR (near infrared light) as well as impedance (conductivity), is to detect early signs of
      diabetic neuropathy.

      The DDD-probe is put directly on the skin and is measuring by the use of light and impedance.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
